Package com.hedera.sdk.common

Class HederaKeySignature

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hedera.sdk.common.HederaKeySignature
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class HederaKeySignature
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class is a helper for managing keys and signatures in tandem. Each instance of the object can store a HederaKeyPair and its corresponding HederaSignature
    See Also:

      • setSignatureForKey

        public boolean setSignatureForKey​(byte[] key,
                                  byte[] signature,
                                  boolean stopAtFirst)
        Sets the signatures against a matching key If they key is found but has signature already set, looks for another matching key If stopAtFirst is true, only the first matching key with no signature is set otherwise all matching keys with no signature are set
        Parameters:
        key - the key to look for
        signature - the signature value to set
        stopAtFirst - sets only the first matching key with empty signature if true
        Returns:
        boolean true if a signature was set

      • setSignatureForKeys

        public boolean setSignatureForKeys​(byte[][] keys,
                                   byte[][] signatures,
                                   boolean stopAtFirst)
        Sets the signatures against matching keys If a key is found but has signature already set, looks for another matching key If stopAtFirst is true, only the first matching key with no signature is set otherwise all matching keys with no signature are set
        Parameters:
        keys - a byte[][] array of keys to look for
        signatures - a byte[][] array of signatures for the keys
        stopAtFirst - sets only the first matching key with empty signature if true
        Returns:
        boolean true if a signature was set

      • setSignatureForKeyUUID

        public boolean setSignatureForKeyUUID​(java.lang.String uuid,
                                      byte[] signature)
        Sets the signature against a key matching the supplied UUID if the signature is already set, it will be overwritten
        Parameters:
        uuid - the UUID of the key to update
        signature - the signature
        Returns:
        boolean true if key was found

      • setSignatureForKeyUUIDs

        public boolean setSignatureForKeyUUIDs​(java.lang.String[] uuids,
                                       byte[][] signatures)
        Sets the signatures against keys matching the supplied UUIDs if the signature is already set, it will be overwritten
        Parameters:
        uuids - a String[] of key UUIDs
        signatures - byte[][] of matching signatures for the UUIDs
        Returns:
        boolean true if a signature was set

        Gets an array of keys and UUIDS HederaKeyUUIDDescription for a given public key
        Parameters:

      • getEntities

        public boolean getEntities​(HederaTransaction payment,
                           HederaQueryHeader.QueryResponseType responseType)
                    throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Runs a query to get entities related to this key from the Hedera Network If successful, the method populates the entityIDs, cost and stateProof for this object depending on the type of answer requested
        Parameters:
        payment - a HederaTransaction message to indicate how this query will be paid for, this can be null for Cost queries
        responseType - the type of response requested from the query
        Returns:
        Boolean indicating success or failure of the query
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException - should an exception occur during communication with the node
